fields.description:
Instances are currently restored incorrectly as the machine image identifier is incorrect in the response from the cluster controller:

{code}
Fri Mar 14 16:19:14 2014 ERROR [VmInstance:Eucalyptus.bootstrap:Callbacks:class com.eucalyptus.util.async.Callbacks$BasicCallbackProcessor.class java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor$Worker#113] [com.eucalyptus.vm.VmInstance$RestoreAllocation.restoreBootSet(VmInstance.java):616] Using transient bootset in place of imageId dsk-9df3bc6b-6a708476, kernelId eki-6af0d23d, ramdiskId eri-52b21d7c for i-e6f1c78b because of: Failed to lookup image named: dsk-9df3bc6b-6a708476
{code}

The cloud controller currently expects that the identifier is the 'emi-...' identifier supplied when running the instance.

The restored instance will show an incorrect image as would occur when restoring and instance for which the image is no longer available:

{code}
# euca-describe-instances
RESERVATION	r-e00ccda1	616678769423	default
INSTANCE	i-e6f1c78b	emi-00000000	euca-10-111-103-26.eucalyptus.b-27.autoqa.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com	euca-172-26-68-171.eucalyptus.internal	running		0		m1.small	2014-03-14T23:19:14.910Z	PARTI00				monitoring-disabled	10.111.103.26	172.26.68.171			instance-store					paravirtualized			sg-de54936e			
TAG	instance	i-e6f1c78b	euca:node	10.111.1.40
{code}

comments.body:
The issue occurred on restore of a paravirtual instance from an instance-store image. The example describe instances response looks correct:

{quote}
<n:id>emi-2a66ac4a</n:id>
{quote}

perhaps this issue does not occur for different virtualization or image types (or has been addressed by changes since this issue was opened)
